OL,3,CIreland rugby star Jack Kyle to be
OL,4,Ccommemorated with blue plaque
OL,6,FAged just 23, and still studying to be
OL,7,Fa doctor, Kyle was selected for the
OL,8,F1950 Lions tour of Australia and New
OL,9,FZealand, where he entranced the home
OL,10,Fcrowds with his instinctive style of
OL,11,Fplay.
OL,13,FJack Kyle, or Jackie as he was
OL,14,Faffectionately known, was born on
OL,15,FFebruary 10 1926 on the Antrim Road in
OL,16,FBelfast.
OL,18,FHe went to Belfast Royal Academy and
OL,19,Fplayed for Ulster Schools and club
OL,20,Frugby for Queen's and North (now
OL,21,FHarlequins).
