OL,3,CIreland rugby star Jack Kyle to be
OL,4,Ccommemorated with blue plaque
OL,6,FEdmund van Esbeck, author of the
OL,7,Fdefinitive history of Irish rugby,
OL,8,Fwrote that prominent among Ireland's
OL,9,Fstrengths was "the sheer genius of
OL,10,FJack Kyle, surely among the greatest
OL,11,Fof all rugby players".
OL,13,FKyle's international career lasted
OL,14,Funtil 1958 in which time he gained 46
OL,15,Fcaps with Ireland and played in six
OL,16,FTests for the Lions.
OL,18,FHe was a member of the Ulster team
OL,19,Fthat dominated the Interprovincial
OL,20,Fseries in the 1950s and was made an
OL,21,FOBE in 1959.
